description:
Francesco Farfa has got his groove back. In recent times, the Italian DJ has found himself re-energised once again, back in love with electronic music and right back at the sharp end of the underground scene. A true digger and sound obsessive, Farfa comes armed with decades of experience and musical appreciation, but now with a fresh perspective that means he is once again doing what he does best: turning musical emotions and compelling rhythms into dance floor art.

The Florence born DJ first started playing as far back as the 90s, laying down vital sets of funk, disco and proto-house sounds. His deck skills and rare knack for selection and sequencing meant he soon became one of Italy’s most famous DJ exports, with his unique skills earning him sets at some of the most prestigious night venues and festivals, such as Space (Ibiza), Amnesia (Ibiza), E-Werk (Berlin), Vinyl (New York), Sonar (Barcelona), Love Parade (Berlin), Monegros (Fraga), Street Parade (Zurich) and many more.

From a production perspective, Farfa has released on the likes of Momento, Souvenir and Serial Killer, always evolving with each new 12″. Timeless sounds that always leave an impression, Farfa’s records have earned a renaissance of late thanks to the support of numerous high-profile players from the scene.

Farfa’s music has been called everything from psychedelic techno to cyber-trance, but it is impossible to truly define, with Farfa instead going in whatever direction his heart takes him. Hugely respected in his native country, Farfa has influenced a whole host of Italian DJs, with none other than Francesco Del Garda among those who continue to cite him as a major influence. Now, it is Del Garda who is inspiring Farfa, and in fact the pair have plans for a special back-to-back series that will see them join forces in the not-too-distant future. After a period of reflection and finding new inspirations, Francesco Farfa is back where he belongs: deep in the underground, playing challenging and unpredictable sets of slick and sleek house, techno and minimal.

Hailing from the New York house scene, DJ/Producer Kai has gained a strong reputation his house/techno styled DJ sets and floor filling dance productions.  As testament to his skills, Grammy winning duo Deep Dish have said, "Kai's track 'Suffocation' is simply amazing. Its one of the best tribal tracks out there" With his tracks getting support from Deep Dish, Sasha & Digweed, Hernan Cattaneo, Desyn Masiello and Danny Howells (just to name a few), Kai’s production ability is synonymous with quality.  The DJ with one of the finest ears in the industry, Desyn Masiello has been quoted as saying Kai’s productions are “brilliant!!”  Already a name growing in demand, Kai has played at some of the world’s best venues including Crobar (NYC), Pacha and the legendary Womb in Tokyo.  

Sasha invited Kai to play at a very special VIP boat party in NYC for a charity benefit.  This is not the first time the A-list jocks have sought out the DJ ability of Kai.  At Crobar NYC, Kai also opened up for Sander Kleinenberg which resulted in rave reviews of his set on all of the internet forums.  Kai has also opened for Roger Sanchez for his “RELEASE YOURSELF” event further cementing Kai’s status as a DJ on the rise.

In John Digweed’s words “Kai has been making some great tracks over the years…  [Kai’s] really starting to find his feet and he’s an excellent DJ as well.”  Kai has proven Digweed right on the last three Yoshitoshi tours of Asia covering over 14 different cities including Tokyo, Hong Kong, Taipei, Seoul, Jakarta, and Singapore.  

Kai has recently joined forces with fellow Asian producer and composer, Kyle to form Kai & Kyle. Kai & Kyle have worked together on many other projects together at various stages of their careers and are very excited at this new chapter of their lives. As a duo they have recently signed to world renowned Toolroom Records for their first single ‘Love No Limit’ featuring an epic remix package graced with remixes by the legendary Kerri Chandler.

Kai is also proud to be a contributor to the very last release on Hooj Choons with his remix of Aphasia - Acapulco will being played by Sasha for his encores to this day.

Working with his former studio partner as Chris & Kai, the two found quick success with an original debut release of “Suffocation/Catch Me” on Yoshitoshi Recordings.  Following the Yoshitoshi release with several critically acclaimed remixes on Hooj Choons, and Yo!, Chris & Kai established themselves as cutting edge producers.  Chris & Kai's productions have been making waves on BBC Radio One with Pete Tong playing their forthcoming release on Alternative Route, "Gone to Heaven," several times on his Essential Selection.  The mighty Sasha & Digweed also feature the same track as the closing song to their Essential Mix live from Renaissance, UK.  “Catch Me” was also included on the Ultra Dance 05 CD compilation that reached #1 on the Billboard Dance Charts in the US.
Kai’s strong DJ sensibilities shine through on his original productions, all having caught the attention and DJ support of many A-list DJs such as Sasha, John Digweed, Luke Fair, Desyn Masiello, Deep Dish, D:Fuse, Danny Howells, Jimmy Van M, and Sander Kleinenberg just to name a few.   Come hear why all the top international jocks are paying attention!

description:
Siddhu and Diana Ayanna are no strangers to the music industry. Their love of music, textural rhythms, fashion, glamour, mysticism, and all things artistic, led them to merge forces and create the Kama Sutra Lovers as an avatar for their creative energies.

This hot new duo is exploring new dimensions of DJ'ing and live electronic music on stage using drum machines, synths, live vocals, and laptops running Ableton Live.

With these elements, the Kama Sutra Lovers not only reference the history of modern electronic music performance and DJ culture, but move into it's next phase: the exciting combination of live performance using drum machines, synths, and vocals, with on the fly remixing and deconstruction of tracks on a granular level with micro loops.

All new Kinky Electric Noise DJ mixes can be found at Mixcloud and Heathis, links below.

Welcome to the Black Feather Files, a spin-off label of the Black Feather series on Black Bridge Recordings and the Black Feather radio show, hosted by label owner Ivy. It’s not your father’s electronic dance music label as the Black Feather Files aim to explore different edges and angles of the genre. These files expose cosmic excursions, disco-influenced devilry, and well-crafted ‘songs’ riding side-by-side in the brightly painted groove jalopy.

Our weekly radio show, Black Feather Radio, on Radioglobal.org (Tijuana, Mexico), focuses heavily on the sounds we dig. The show airs live 9pm-11pm MST, every Thursday night. Tune in at:

Mark DelMedico is a solo acoustic musician.Mark plays classic/folk/rock ,Playing both original and cover songs.

Mark started playing guitar in 1975,by 1978 he was writing  his own songs as well as playing many covers in bars and coffee houses in central NY.In 1980 Mark formed an acoustic duo with Jim Prichard,they were called Dark Horse ,they performed together until 1982 when Jim left to form a band.Mark was asked to join the band but declined,so he could keep playing as an acoustic act.Mark gave up live performing from 1985 until around  2003 when he started performing here and there.Now he is getting back into it as a full time thing.

   Spring of 2008 Mark  decided to record 10 of his original songs,he was looking for a place to record ,mentioned it to a guy he had met several times that is a very popular musician in the central NY area by the name of jon Liebing. Jon offered to produce and record the songs at his home studio Mark played acoustic guitar and sang lead.Jon also played acoustic and electric guitars,piano,bass,drums,harmonica,tambourine and sang harmony.The recordings were finished in June the cd should be out in September or October of 2008  .

The original music Mark writes,has been described as a mixture of  folk/rock/country music not too country (think Neil Young,Tom Petty) I have heard people say his music reminds them of a mix of Beatles/Dylan/Lou Reed/Tom Petty and Neil Young  which isn`t too far off the Mark.
Echo Inspectors are Mark Baumann and Lance Harrison From Melbourne, Australia. Lurking in the shadows, inspired by all that is dark, hidden and mysterious.

We wanna go somewhere else. We're not threatened by people anymore. All our insecurities have evaporated. We're in the clouds now. We're wide open. We're spacemen orbiting the earth. The world looks beautiful from here, man. We're nympholeptics, desiring for the unobtainable. We risk sanity for moments of temporary enlightenment. So many ideas. So little memory. The last thought killed by anticipation of the next. We embrace an overwhelming feeling of love. We flow in unison. We're together. I wish this was real. We want a universal level of togetherness, where we're comfortable with everyone. We're in rhythm. Part of a movement. A movement to escape. We wave goodbye. Ultimately, we just want to be happy. Heh, yeah, hang on, what the fuck was I just talking about?

- Human Traffic, 1999

To acknowledge that we live on the tropic has its advantages. Getting back to reality where we are the sewage of a world where theories melt away under the sun and get new shapes makes us accept our own creativity, naturally and unattached.
                To live in the tropic makes us wish endlessly to come up with ways to deal with our shortcomings and break the boundaries to express ourselves. The tropic means one step behind anything that implies solid and withstanding infrastructures, schemes or systems.
                Wherever there was a house before, there is a shopping center today, and tomorrow there will be a flea market, or nothing at all. Cockfighting clubs become police stations; and boulevards, indigents flats.
                Hence, to create, to invent, to share, to recicle, are ways to replace and give sense to our tropicality.
                This wheather molds us and fuses us into a community where rules melt away.
                This is where our community becomes, in accepting this tropical reality and intensifying it, in admitting that creation is short-term lasting, and for this reason it shouldnt have owner other than that who receives it; to acknowledge that value resides in usefulness, to let others receive, love and create from your work.
                At Digital Audio Tropical Archives, we are aware of this, we believe that our work should be shared, listened, digested, molded and spread out, by others like us.
                Here, the value resides in to reach, to akcnowledge and to transform.

Javier Martínez siempre ha concebido la producción musical como base de su estilo de vida desde que se iniciara profesionalmente en la industria y sin que la discapacidad auditiva con la que nació truncara los sueños y objetivos del que ahora conocemos como Ctrls303.

Tras un tiempo retirado, regresa en 2008 a las cabinas de numerosos clubes de ciudades como Barcelona, Ibiza, Madrid, Almería o Berlín, entre otras, aportando al panorama de la electrónica una selección musical renovada y con mucha personalidad, bajo unas líneas coherentes que evocan al Deep y al Dub Techno, bajo un sentido sonido Detroit.

En 2010, inmerso en la producción da vida a Submoover Records, el sello discográfico de Deep Techno, Dub Techno y Techno junto a Toni Martínez, con importantes lanzamientoscomo Tiritatucan - Tiritatucan EP,  Dany Angelelli – Alchemy of Technology EP,  Analog People – The True EP, entre muchos otros.

Tras dos años de duro trabajo, en 2012 Javier es diagnosticado Retinosis Pigmentaria Síndrome de Usher de tipo II (Sordoceguera), una enfermedad rara sin cura a día de hoy que afecta tanto la visión como la audición, lo que le deja fuera del mundo de la producción, asimilando así su destino.

Sin embargo, en 2018 y con el ansia de más que nunca expresar sus sentimientos, Martínez toma las riendas de su futuro para volver a componer y producir música electrónica en una combinación de talento y tesón que nos traerá a principios del próximo año 2019, como resultado, sus nuevos y más intensos proyectos musicales bajo el alias de Ctrls303y auspiciados bajo el exigente sello discográfico Rhod Records. Sin límites.

Porque querer es siempre poder.

De Nachtdokter (Raldi van Trappe) is de eigenaar van de Nachtdokters een succesvol bedrijf in Hilversum Centrum.
Deze Dj, Producer, Mc en evenementen organisator laat weinig aan het toeval over. Zo begon hij zijn eigen bedrijf de Nachtdokters op 4 juli 2012 met het plan als in eigen beheer te houden. Hij deelde zijn bedrijf in 3 delen DJ  School Hilversum, boekingsbureau en evenementen organisatie om zo zijn eigen talentvolle leerlingen binnen zijn bedrijf te kunnen plaatsen. Ook producer lessen en studio werkzaamheden vallen onder zijn beheer.
Als dj is hij een laatbloeier en is hij 1 van de hardst stijgende dj's van DJGuide op het moment en hoort hij bij de top 50 van beste dj's.
Zijn stijl is afwisselend en hij voelt zijn publiek goed aan. Zijn sterke kanten zijn vooral de kwaliteit van het geluid en zijn positieve en liefdevolle uitstraling.
Zijn zwakke punt is dat zijn perfectionisme hem vaak in de weg staat en dat hij graag iedereen zijn aandacht wil geven wat zeer veel tijd in beslag neemt.
Deze duizendpoot is al vanaf zijn 17e jaar bezig met muziek en heeft al vele optredens op zijn naam staan zowel nationaal als internationaal. Grote evenementen zoals Dance Valley, Mysteryland en Clubs als de Mazzo, 020, Rothaanhuis, Melkweg en de Paradiso staan op zijn naam.

Styles : Mellow House, House, Progressive House, Deep House, Hip Hop, Soul, 80s, 90s en World Music.

    L' "electro-phunk" band formata da 5 ragazzi umbri (Ricc,Lapo,Mac,Master,Gimbo) partecipa nel 2003 ad Arezzo Wave come band emergente tra 1400 formazioni.
    Risulta la migliore band del festival e si aggiudica la produzione del primo album: “United Condom” e di un videoclip.
    Nel 2004 sono ospiti speciali dello stesso festival aretino, questa volta sul palco del Main Stage, al fianco di Little Louie Vega e Groove Armada.
    Nel 2005 sono tra le 10 migliori band Europee (unici italiani) a partecipare al reality show: “Mtv A Cut” girato a Londra con Anastacia, Wade Robson e Olivier Behezadi.
    L’esperienza inglese matura un progetto al quale tengono da tempo: lavorare con testi in italiano.
    Il nuovo ed atteso disco dei Frost, in prossima uscita, segnerà un’altra tappa fondamentale nella storia del gruppo.
    
    Hanno fatto da spalla a:
    -Bugo, Amari, Yuppie Flu, Thank You For The Drum Machine, The Toy Orchestra, Karate, Z-star, Little Louie Vega (Master at Work) & his Elements of Life, Shit Disco, Soul II Soul, Groove Armada (Main Stage dell' Arezzo Wave Love Festival), Dirty Feel, The Hormonauts, Pram, Pulseprogramming, Nouvelle Vague, Kings of Convenience...
    
    Hanno suonato come musicisti con:
    -Loredana Bertè, Horacio El Negro Hernandez, Robbie Ameen, Denise La Cruz (Master at Work), Yosvany Terry, Buena Vista Social Club, Roy Hargrove , Denise La Cruz, Robbie Ameen, Cristiano Arcelli ,The Neville Brothers, Dr. Bone & The Hepcats, Robert Lopez, Funk Off, Rockin’ Dopsie & The Zydeco Twisters, Derek Trucks (Eric Clapton's guitarrist) ecc...
    
    Hanno suonato come Dj (Frost Dj Sexx) con:
    -Erlend Oye, Bugo, My Owesome Mixtape, Ex-Otago, Amari, Claudio Coccoluto, Ralf, Tiger Tiger!,GG...
    
    Hanno vinto:
    -Arezzo Wave Love Festival 2003 come migliore band emergente, presentato l'album"United Condom" sul palco del Main Stage 2004 prima di Little Loue Vega e Groove Armada.
    -Le selezioni italiane per il programma televisivo "MTV A CUT". Dopo questa esperienza, hanno partecipato al reality music-show ai Premises Studios a Londra tra le dieci migliori bands europee (Trasmesso in tutta Europa).
    
    "Frost Dj Sexx" è il progetto parallelo dell'electro pop band "Frost". Il duo è composto da Ricc, LApo, laptop, synth e drum machines. Si esibiscono dal vivo in vivaci e pimpati dj set dove nascono remix in tempo reale, mash up in perfetto stile "Italian post new wave".

Homo Simulacrum is electronic music composer from Lithuania who currently resides in London. I am working with sound and its relationship with the new technologies. I'm in love with sounds, but more importantly, I love to create music from these souns. The possibilities are endless, therefore my main intention is to provide the listener with the perspective that would allow her/him to explore the creative possibilities of sound production. I would assume, that like any other musician, I create from the experiences of the everyday life. From the music's point of view, I am influenced by Electroacoustic Music, Musique Concrète, Deutche Elektronische Musik, Glitch, contemporary dance music such as Techno, House, Hip-Hop, Dubstep, Drum and Bass and all the others - too many to mention here. 
At the moment I am composing music that I hope will be heard, appreciated or hated, and hopefully released. Although we live in the internet age, it is exceptionally easy for many musicians to be lost in the data jungle and never be heard. I would appreciate any feedback. Lots of love and good luck. Enjoy.

Hailing from New Zealand, Simon Beeston is one of a select group of producer/DJs from his home country to have achieved success in Europe and around the world in the field of electronic dance music. Influenced by House, Techno and Electronica, it would be difficult to put his music into any one category, but his tracks always have both feet on the dance floor, an irresistible groove and a unique array of samples and sounds. As a DJ Simon plays a bionic mix of Tech House, Deep House and Techno, full of subtle musical hooks and crunchy percussion. His innate ability to program a set from peak time to rolling grooves never fails to keep dancers on the floor. He has played in clubs all over Europe, Asia, Australia, New Zealand and, of course, at home in Berlin, where he has rocked the floors of Panorama Bar, Watergate, Bar25, Katerholzig, Arena Club, Goldengate and almost every other hot spot in the worlds capital of electronic dance music. 

Simon’s music has found it’s way all around the world with the help of several respected record labels and wide international DJ support. He has released tracks and remixes on labels like Thoughtless Music, Highgrade Records, Freizeitglauben, District of Corruption, Nordik Net, Cimelde Records, Igloo, Supdub, and Microzoo.

After 2 years in New Zealand, Simon is now back in his adopted hometown, Berlin.

A true creator, artist, musician, world explorer & adventurer at heart, Charl’s life has been filled with passion & love for music. He’s been shaping the landscape in DXB for the last 17 years as a creative, documenting the history of nightlife culture with his music & nightlife movement, INFUSION MAGAZINE.  Creating innovative concepts like ‘Nasimi Beach Full Moon’ events, influencing musical tastes with his pioneering HOUSEofAFRIKA nights or booking legendary ‘Cypress Hill’ for their first ever show in the UAE, Charl is forever expanding his horizons.  Still one of DXB’s favorite DJ’s, today you will find him committed to his craft by nurturing & developing the next generation of DJs at his INFUSION DJ Factory School, whiles pursuing his vision of ‘ONELOVE’ alongside music & healing modalities ‘ECSTATIC DANCE’ & ‘DEEP HOUSE YOGA DXB’. Committing his life to study the ancient modalities of ritual, sound, meditation, breath work, movement, fire ceremony & indigenous songs, he has grounded himself into his purpose to serve in this honorable way. His ‘OneLove Experience’ is the culmination of his life’s work, a unique mix of music, wellness & adventure retreats, focused on expanding your horizons & upgrading your life through reconnecting to ancient traditions & rituals. Today you will find him pursuing his musical career with 'WISE TRIBE' in San Diego.

CHAKA’S CAREER 
Growing up in a musical family, he’s been collecting records since the age of 16 in Cape Town, SA music circuit in the early 90’s. In 1999 he won a DJ competition & residency at ‘Club Heaven ’ London. It was in 2004 his ambition & eagerness for a challenge found him landing in DXB where his unique mix of musical prowess & innovation, has seen him  receive numerous awards in his career, winning the ‘Technics International DJ Comp’ back in 2006, voted #4 in the ‘DJ Mag Middle East Poll’ of 2010 & winner of ‘Best Local DJ’ in the TimeOut Nightlife Awards 2012 & featured as ‘Best Local DJ’ in numerous Nightlife Awards since then. From back in 2008 being in the 'Ahlan Top 100 influencers' to being presented the ‘Outstanding Contribution Award’ from HYPE Magazine in 2016, it’s easy to see why Charl has been a permanent fixture & house hold name in the DJ booth’s of the Sandance, Creamfields & Yas Arena main stages, to legendary clubs like ‘360’,’iBO’ & his infamous ‘Deep Nights’ Trilogy Rooftop residency.  Not one to be pigeonholed he has proven his versatility & capability as a artist & entertainer by opening for the likes Jamiroquai & LTJ Bukem & is still regularly called upon to play quality music sets from his heart & soul at the likes of Blue Marlin Ibiza UAE, The Hatch, GrooveOnTheGrass, Night Vibes, VII DXB etc. With music in his blood & creativity from his soul, Music is his Life.

Franck Collin, aka Fleck E.S.C, is an Electro artist originally from France currently living in the buzzing metropolis of Tokyo, Japan.
Franck's earlier experience playing bass and drums in bands, and his love of horror, science fiction and B-movies, naturally drove him to
the Electro music scene. Additionally, Fleck E.S.C has influences rooted in New Wave, Contemporary, Techno and Ambient music. Fleck E.S.C tries
to avoid the cliches of the Electro genre, leaning more toward the spooky side of horror and sci-fi and the cheap retro sounds in tribute
of the movies he loves. Never too serious, unpretentious, and always striving for fresh sounds, Fleck E.S.C's music aims to distract the 
body and the brain.

Franck Collin has also worked in movie productions as a camera assistant . He has also created music for Lipton Cafe Shibuya in Tokyo, theatre performances in Berlin, Germany and the soundtrack for the film,"Astroboy in Robotland", by renowned director of "Delicatessen" and "The Lost Children", Marc Caro. He has also performed as Fleck E.S.C in a number of venues in Europe and Japan.

"Inside a cage of sound,  Cold waves of electronics are juxtaposed against voices that seep through cracks in the walls of machinery and wires. Lyrics dart out in bullets from soundscapes peppered in sharp vocals and sound bites. A viola plays in the distance, giving life to this inorganic mass... 
Such is the imagery that spawns Attrition, who, with its marriage of the classic and modern, has brought to music the equivalent of a surrealist painting. From its earlier sparse and stark soundscapes, to a more expansive palette of orchestral work, Attrition has successfully melded several genres into one. The music flows - from gothic to industrial to experimental to classical - so smoothly, they might as well be making their own category. 
With more than twenty albums of constant variety, and an ever-expanding sound, they remain one of music's darker and fascinating lights."  
Akane

Matt Xavier is a New York born & raised psychedelic DJ, producer and event organizer living in Los Angeles. He is a California State certified harm reduction addiction counselor, psychedelic integration specialist and certified cannabis-assisted psychedelic guide through his private practice, Integrated Psychedelics. Since 1993, Matt's contribution to the global electronic music culture has been undeniably psychedelic. In the early 1990's Matt (formerly Matthew Magic)co-founded New York City's first psychedelic trance company, Tsunami Productions, where he served as resident DJ/music director until the turn of the millennium. During that time he shared the stage with such international talents as Juno Reactor, Hallucinogen, X-Dream, KoxBox, Son Kite, GMS, Total Eclipse, Slinky Wizard and Green Nuns of the Revolution. Soon after he retired the format and began producing deep techno, house and progressive under the moniker "Gruvhaus", with releases & remixes appearing on such labels as Fabric, Release Records, Polyester Music, Fugu and Chug Records. In 2005 Matt founded the internationally acclaimed techno label Railyard Recordings, who attracted such talents as Joel Mull, Cari Lekebusch, Alexi Delano, Donato Dozzy, Adultnapper, and Mathew Jonson, to name a few. Since his 2003 arrival in Los Angeles, Matt has held the role of resident DJ/music director at Subtract Music, Compression, and $2 Tuesday's as well as continued to present his brand of psychedelic house, trippy techno and ambient-chillout at such notable events/venues as Lightning in a Bottle, Moontribe, Symbiosis, Giant, Spundae, Avalon, Vanguard, 1015 Folsom, Circus Disco and King King Hollywood.

We Were Pirates is the musical brainchild of Mike Boggs, a multi-instrumentalist who writes and records songs in his home studio in the DC area. Boggs has released three albums, an EP, and a film score for ‘Dear Mr. Watterson.’

Boggs’ 2009 debut album, Cutting Ties, features a version of ‘The Three of Us,’ a cover song that Boggs recorded which was featured on the public radio show, This American Life. Greg Kot, Chicago Tribune rock critic and co-host of Sound Opinions described the cover as, “Pure pop.” And said, “This should be the next Fountains of Wayne single; genius.”

Wired magazine featured We Were Pirates following the release of the second album, Change. The feature said, “You heard this band’s public radio-friendly pop on This American Life...So don’t miss ‘Better Off Without You’ from the new album. Catchy synths will have your crew dancing a jig.”

In 2013, Boggs wrote and recorded an original film score for ‘Dear Mr. Watterson.’ The film is a documentary about the impact of the comic strip, Calvin & Hobbes. This American Life featured We Were Pirates again, when they played ‘A Strange Experience’ from the film score on Episode 512. We Were Pirates performed songs from ‘Dear Mr. Watterson’ live at screenings of the film.

On 2016’s Matter, Boggs explores a mellow, electronic aesthetic. Following the release, NPR’s Morning Edition interviewed Boggs and We Were Pirates bassist, Kate Rears Burgman. The band also played a string of live shows, including one at The Kennedy Center in DC.

We Were Pirates is starting out 2019 by releasing a new EP that finds Boggs returning to a more organic sound. Gone features five new songs about the pursuit of love, pain, and peace of mind. TW Walsh (Pedro the Lion) mastered the album.

We Were Pirates live shows feature Burgman on bass, Pat Frank on drums, and Scott Greenberg playing guitar.

BRIAN SALAZAR 
(Endup, Soul Camp, Housemen)

At a very young age, when most were just learning about the birds and the bees, Brian was, already, learning how to build and keep dance floors.  At the age of 12, his older sister, Maryann, taught him how to spin vinyl since her boyfriend, at the time, was in a mobile DJ group, Unique Musique, and they used their parents garage as storage for all the DJ equipment, crates of vinyl, speakers, lighting, truss bars, etc.  Although Brian started off playing freestyle, very soon after, he became the newest member of the mobile DJ group, at the age of 14, and started handling the old school hip hop sets at weddings, school dances, hall parties, house parties, and even a few small clubs/bars (he was only allowed to stay behind the decks and in the backroom since he was under age).

After, truly & thoroughly, experiencing the West Coast rave scene in the 90s, he fell deep in love with house music and, quickly, worked his way up the local dj circuit through hours & hours of record shopping, strategic networking, event planning, and rigorous self promotion. 

In the most opportune environment, Brian Salazar has taken from the depths of the dance floor to cavernous record crates and created a sound all his own. More groovy, moveable, and undeniable than most, it is in his capacity to interact and control the sound setting that keeps fans crawling back at 5am and beyond.  In the past decade and a half, Brian Salazar has advanced from his first major underground event to getting signed by Devotion Records, getting signed by Meow Ent., getting signed by Undefeated, going on his first International tour in Asia, going on tour with Kaskade, playing at the Winter Music Conference in Miami multiple seasons, playing the Love Parade back to back years, playing live on radio stations such as WILD 94.9, KZSU 90.1, VAULT RADIO 104.9, MAGIC 89.9 (Phillipines), playing on internet shows such as centricmusic.com, pressureradio.com, ssradiouk.com, dive radio, undefeated sessions, and d3ep radio network, starting his own house collective called the HOUSEMEN, starting his own female house collective called the HOUSEWIVES, and becoming a resident at the legendary Endup where he has thrown several monthly events, consistently, for the past 14+ years straight. To add to his movement, currently, he is the main man behind ELEMENTS OF HOUSE After Hours and co-founder of the annual campout, Soul Camp.

Years of commitment to soul searching, ear tuning, collecting vinyl, and downloading gives him the ideal collection to cater and command crowds at any hour, at any event, venue, city, or country. This incredible rise derives from the flirtatious vocals, intellectual instrument solos, and groovy bass lines he brings together, flawlessly, during any and every set.

"I choose my tracks from a spectator point of view, and not just as a dancer, DJ, or a musician. I want anyone from any musical background to walk into my set and be instantly submerged". Dedicated to music as a whole from jazz, disco, soul, R&B, funk, reggae, old school, rap, classical, and salsa, Brian Salazar has fine-tuned his ear to introduce a sound that is refreshing, intellectual, and catchy.  Additionally, the background of being a dancer has elevated his perspective on music selection and solidified his reputation as a crowd pleaser. "A dancer-turned-dj knows what to play to make people dance."

With over 30 years under his belt, Brian has proven that he has a keen sense of diversified soul and a deep understanding that track selection, skills, programming, promotion, and solid people & communication skills, while being honest & humble, are essential.  Considered a sleeping giant, he introduces himself to the world as the next prolific movement to change a culture and uplift a generation.

Follow him at...
https://www.facebook.com/brian.salazar.509
https://www.instagram.com/mrbriansalazar/

There's not many in today's scene whose music you can instantly recognize, but Jay Vegas has quickly become one of them, having developed his own unique twisted disco sound.

Jay started his career in the early 90’s as a session keyboardist, he’d come up with catchy hooks for local producers. Most noteble was his killer piano riff on K-Klass’s remix of Bobby Brown – Two Can Play That Game.

Towards the end of the 90’s Jay teamed up with ex Mr Peach (Olympic Records) member James Ryan. They worked under the various aliases including: Soundscapers and Nu Graduates. Their productions and remixes appeared on labels such as Subliminal, Ministry of Sound, Cream, Fantasia & Cleveland City. Jay and James were one of the first UK artist to appear on Erick Morillo’s iconic label Subliminal. Their remix of Kaya – My God is Real was Pete Tong’s ‘Essential New Tune’ on BBC Radio 1. 

In 1999 Jay released ‘Tribal Chant’ on London based label Kingpin. This was the conception of his solo alias Jay Vegas. 

In 2011 Jay joined San Francisco’s Guesthouse Music, settling in amongst a roster of hugely talented artists such as: DJ Sneak, Gramophonedzie, Sonny Fodera, Gene Farris, DJ Dan and DJ Mes. 

Since conception Jay’s funky style has been well received, gaining support from some of the industry's biggest names including: David Morales, Mark Knight, Erick Morillo, Mousse T, Norman Cook, Junior Vasquez, Danny Rampling and Grant Nelson. Grant Nelson in particular helped push his sound by regularly featuring Jay's tracks on his Housecall Radio Show.

Jay has remixed for an array of artists: Todd Terry, DJ Chus, Harry Romero, Gene Farris & Joeski. His music has appeared on all the major compilations including: Ministry of Sound & Hed Kandi.

As well as holding down a busy DJ schedule, Jay also runs his own imprint Hot Stuff Records. It's already become a firm favourite with DJ's, having released a string of Traxsource #1's with his own tracks: Say To Ya, Luv Drug, Come Soon & Body & Soul.  

Jay's musical taste knows no boundaries and is not restricted by genre - his "If it's good, I'll play it" mentality has took him around the world playing at some of the best clubs; from Ibiza to as far as Australia.

If you like your music funky, energetic and exciting check out Jay Vegas!

We are a 2 piece electronic music outfit. I am Darren and have been producing music for 10 years now. It started with a Roland MC303 in 1997 in a flat in the depths of Birmingham, England. Shortly afterwards I bought a PC and started recording my 303 vibes into Soundforge. I remember it well, I would find a sound I liked, then sequence it up using a specific BPM, record it to Soundforge then do the same over and over until I got what I wanted. Things have moved on a bit since then technology wise, but the basic principle remains the same. To make music I like. Amanda came from a VERY different musical background . From an early age she loved to sing and perform. Though these days prefers to concentrate on the creative side of music making. From time to time Amanda would get involved in writing music, however, she was never able to find the write producer, until now that is. Amanda is now enjoying being given the chance to be a lyricist and create her own melodies.

DJ / Producer George Cross’ love of dance music erupted when Rave dropped in the early 90s. He began to develop an obsession with hardcore, house, garage and underground techno, especially Colin Dale's ‘Outer Limits’ show on KISS FM, Fantazia, and nights at the UK's legendary south coast venues Sterns, Zanies and Golden Hill Fort. 

This passion led to George DJing in local clubs, sourcing new music any which way he could. Big influences over the years include Aphex Twin, Jeff Mills, Carl Craig, Trans Europe Express, Luke Slater and Basic Channel, which is evident in his production and DJ sets. 

After the success of 'Spark' [SKM004], which received 8/10 in top dance music magazine iDJ, gigs were soon secured across Europe, including a night sponsored by Nixon Watches at Portugal’s oldest nightclub. 

George's music has been supported by top DJs Dave Clarke, Brendon Moeller, Tania Vulcano and Cristian Varela, to name but a few. 

iDJ reviewer Lee Smith compared his sound to Carl Craig’s BFC era, recommending “Fans of Redshape, Black Dog and other classically inclined types should investigate forthwith”.

Is this Techno? 

Perhaps, but it comes at you with a sly, subtle wink, a shuffled gait and a lopsided smile. An assuredness that makes you both nervous and intrigued. It commands your focus. Like a homeless person begging for change in a smart neighbourhood, the contrast is intriguing. There's character, underneath the dirt. An otherness you almost connect with, a sound to be fascinated by, a pile of rags you can't stop staring at.

This is handmade electronic music. Straight from the heart of Aidan Morrison / Fear Of The Rave. Hackney dweller, citizen of the world, lover of techno, house music and booty shaking bass. 

Bringer of the rave, in all it's fearsome, noisy, sweaty glory.

description:
If someone is dealing with deephouse, techno and dubmusic the probability is high to come across the name of Mandy Jordan. It is definitively not possible to pigeonhole her music as it is sometimes profound and very often minimal, hypnotic and just refreshing. She’s always keeping track on everything that’s going on in her musical surroundings and she also likes to have a look back into the past. Finally Mandy likes music which resides between techno and house. She is one of the kinds who formed and developed minimal techno especially in the eastern part of Germany. In the end that’s really not surprising as she and her boyfriend Daniel are having their own record and mp3 label for minimal and house music since already five years. Therefore Vekton Music and Vee Recordings became a very important part of her life. Since she turned 15 she went regularly to partys where she always got the main inspiration for her work. Mandy was born in Görlitz and she spent her youth in a couple of different cities in Germany. After she finished her studies of economics successfully she moved to Kamenz which is located pretty close to the main city of Dresden. In Kamenz she’s also having her office and appendant studio. Here she’s working on her music, taking care of all the label work as well as coordinating all of the bookings.

www.vekton.de

With such a varied background and musical taste complimented with extraordinary talent, it is easy to see why Dimitris has become a very bright light in the dj community.

description:
Hello! I'm David Rondón a truly music lover. 

I've been working as a music producer, DJ, radio and TV Host for over 18 years.

Living in Miami, but originally from Caracas I hold a degree in audio engineering and Music Business from SAE Institute in Barcelona, Spain.

As a DJ I've been working in the Venezuelan and international electronic music scene, sharing stage with DJ's like Felix Da Housecat, Miss Kittin, Hercules and Love Affair among others and traveling around the world to play in cities like New York, St Barths, Barcelona, Madrid, Bogota, Aruba and Miami of course. For the past 10 years I produce with DJ Trujillo a soire call “VOYAGE” a French retro-futuristic music journey of sounds and pleasure, a sexy party where you can dance from disco to the newest trends. I love Disco, Classic House, Re Edits and happy music.

I’m a radio man. For almost 2 decades I’ve being in working in radio, broadcasting nation wide in Venezuela. First at La Mega 107.3 FM in Caracas, hosting and producing “Scratch” an eclectic music show where I ride from classic sounds to new trends. Thanks to Scratch I've brought together young musicians to make music compilations of Venezuelan artists, leading them to achieve great commercial success while always betting on new sounds. Now I'm running a new Radio Station Circuito Líder FM and you can tune us weekdays from 5 to 7 pm.

Music Journalism is and important part of my career. I made many TV reports, interviewing musicians like Richie Hawtin, Soulwax, Justice, Yelle, WhoMadeWho, The Horrors, The Roux, Mad Professor, Ewan Pearson, Rory Phillips among others for HBO Latin America and E! Entertainment Latin America. In the past I have work as a TV host for Sony Entertainment TV Latin America doing "Music News" and for RCTV (Venezuela) doing “Sonoclips”.

Other outstanding works done by David Rondon:

- Producer for the British Council's Incubator program, designing strategies for the musical exchange between UK and Latin America.

- Spokesman of the Red Bull Music Academy, guiding new musicians on how they can participate in the academy doing tours nationally.

- International Young Music Entrepreneur finalist by The British Council.

- Coordinator of the Red Bull Music Academy Radio 2011 in Madrid.

Albert is the producing part of Danish hip-hop duo Benal, who has released three succesful records and reached 40 million accumulative streams on Spotify with their top 10 tracks.
 
On his solo-project, Albert returns to instrumental electronica, uniquely fusing modern pop elements with underground club music and adding vocals from well-known Danish artists.  
 
Albert’s self-titled debut album dives into nostalgia, exploring the producer’s youth and the millennial club culture that shaped him artistically, musically, and mentally. 
 
The new album is created alongside Rune Rask, Olle Häggberg and Emil Simonsen from Denmark’s biggest hip-hop group Suspekt, making Albert a part of their producer/label powerhouse TABU Records.

Clash The Disko Kids a.k.a Kurt, is known for his hand picked selection of only the finest in underground experimental disco, house, & techno. With absolutely no intention of pleasing the mainstream party posers, he defiantly stick by his morals to feed the passionate techno and disco heads with brain sizzling tracks that never fail to satisfy. Meanwhile, his tracks have already received support by industry heavyweights such as Bart B More, NT89, Dem Slackers, Shameboy, Style of Eye, Malente, Supabeatz, Gtronic, Sound of Stereo, Sharem Jey and Mumbai Science to name a few. Heavily influenced by the Belgian-German techno sounds, his tracks will keeps the clubbers dancing and shuffling till they dropped. 

Leaving the crappy bubble gum commercial music to the amateurs, this Disko Kid doesn’t rely on a big crowd to promise a good party. As a self proclaimed nocturnal being, Kurt prefers to keep his activities out of the sun and behind the decks, dedicating his free time locked up in his personal asylum while concocting bpm blasting, ear bleeding mixes to please his loyal followers.

Fifteen years ago, deeply entrenched in Berlin’s hip hop and graffiti cultures, Florian Andres bought his first Technics 1200 turntable. Infected by the burgeoning early 2000’s Berlin club scene, he discovered electronic music and a complete new way of partying in underground clubs. He found his home in clubs like WMF, RIO, Skala, Villa, Cookies and Tape, as well as the Berlin art and fashion scenes.
Active in the music scene for quite some time now, always catching up with new trends and challenging audiences. For him, the key to a successful DJ-set lies in finding the right approach on interacting with the audience. Florian guides them with profound musical knowledge and diverse DJ skills. Apart from being a DJ, Florian Andres produces his own music releasing on Apersonal Music.
Stay tuned for more exiting projects and releases.

ALPHA V is Valentina Torelli , a historic Milanese DJ and producer who began to grapple with turntables since the early 90s . Spinning vinyl records with the first GuidanceKru , she dancefloor sound drum'n'bass shaken ; was the golden age of the legendary Pergola and she was a true pioneer who , alongside his friend and colleague Lady Hellen , boasts the first female representations of the scene drum'n'bass Italian .

Over the years he has collaborated on many projects , including the joint venture with Royalize ( d ' n'b side of Casino Royale ) always be involved in several initiatives focused on DJing female females as 100 % Woman Sound and participation in events Female Cut .

His musical journey has been an evolution , opening the way to new sonic territory with a matrix influenced by techno and house , soulfunk and electro.

After four years in Rome , Alpha V is back the beloved Milan bringing new enthusiasm and energy ... ready to explode in his passionate DJ sets , where it merges with the dark soul a refined style and technical skills unmistakable .

Alpha-V nasce artisticamente nel 1997 a Milano, esperienza condivisa fin dagli esordi con Lady Hellen. Accomunate dalla stessa passione per la musica, si costruiscono uno spazio all’interno delle serate Guidance 21th Century, della GuidanceKru. Cavalcando l’entusiasmo e la passione che la contraddistinguono, abilmente “ mixate” con uno stile decisamente duro e tagliente Alpha-V e l’amica/collega Hellen vantano le prime performance al “ femminile” nella scena drum & bass in Italia. L’esperienza nel tempo le permetterà di conoscere e suonare direttamente con artisti internazionali di grosso calibro. La presenza di Alpha-V non si limita soltanto alla dance hall ma partecipa inoltre come ospite fissa per svariati anni al programma radiofonico “ Guida nella Giungla” curato dalla GuidanceKru sulle frequenze di Radio Popolare Network. L’ anno 2000 vede nascere la collaborazione tra Alpha-V, Lady Hellen e i Royalize, legando così il loro nome al progetto drum’n bass dei Casino Royale e partecipando a numerosi eventi in tutta Italia. Sempre nel 2000 da una co-produzione con Dr. Pauli dei Royalize, nasce il singolo “Sound Witch Project” pubblicato dalla prima etichetta D’n’B indipendente milanese: Shee Been. L’artista ha riscoperto da molti anni le sonorità morbide e accattivanti della musica elettronica. E soprattutto del genere house e minimal techno Questo contesto le offre la possibilità di cimentarsi e sperimentare anche in questo stile, suonando nei migliori club e discoteche della penisola. Nel 2005 si impegna in un progetto musicale, dal nome “Milano Clubbing” per l’etichetta Aries Sound dove la traccia intitolata “Souspicius Valentine” ha riscosso molti consensi. Nel 2006 diventa resident dj per le serate Females 100% Woman Sound, l’unica one night a Milano dominata da sole donne dj e vj, dove Alpha affianca sempre artiste internazionali e italiane di grosso calibro che spaziano dalla deep house alla minimal techno. Nel 2007 in co-produzione con gli Stargarage e Lady Hellen produce l’ EP “Kinotte”, per la rinomata etichetta italiana 303Lovers. Nell’agosto del 2009 da una collaborazione con l’artista Sire-g, produce il remix “Robocop” di Marco Dassi per l’etichetta brasiliana Strike Records. Dal febbraio del 2010 decide di cambiare città e di trasferirsi a Roma per iniziare nuove esperienze musicali ed è infatti in cantiere con nuovi progetti orientata sulle attuali sonorità tech house e deep. 
 Dopo quattro anni a Roma , Alpha V è tornata nell'amata  Milano portando nuovo entusiasmo ed energia ... pronta a esplodere nei suoi appassionati dj-set , dove si fonde l'anima scura con uno stile raffinato e competenze tecniche inconfondibili .

NORMAN CHUNG 
He makes you move but opens your mind, letting you accept a wider spectrum of music and at a level of quality that sets the bar for you thereafter. You realise it is not the floor that dictates what a DJ plays but a DJ like Norman dictating how the people might dance. 
As with any passionate music lover, a time comes when a logical progression is made from DJing to production. His Debut EP took place in 2006, with a Deetron collaboration on the highly respected Sino techno label. Ben Sims proceeded to playlist 2 tracks in his Escapism Pt 2 mix CD and charted by Ken Ishii and Christian Smith. A slew of releases followed on labels such as Plus Tokyo, Funk Me, Crayon. He is currently working with Chicago legend K-Alexi with a remix of “You Are” on Orlando Voorn’s Divine imprint and is part of the “5Kings” collective in his quest to push the musical boundaries further and wider. His latest “Forbidden Planet”E.P has received support from Laurent Garnier, Fabrice Lig, Santiago Salazar, Vince Watson, Dave Mothersole among other notable artists. 
Norman’s aim as a musician is simple: to add to the myriad of good music in existence. For someone who has had the gift of music for so long, it is only about time to give it all back..

A very important part of the core family of #Nitin and #Jonny #White’s imprint #No.#19 Music and head of a successful record label #Louie #Fresco is finally getting the world to notice him.
Mr. Fresco’s music is ethereal, ominous, experimental, yet it goes very well on the dance floor. Having been working on his album for No.19 for 2 years, Louie hadn’t released any original music on any other labels (apart from his own label #MEXA #Records) but he has done some remix damage on so many labels such as #Defected, #Nurvous, #Smoke N Mirrors, #Strictly Rhythm, #Exploited, and a recent remix he did for #Ali #Love on #Dim #Mak Records.

Louie is no stranger to success (his remix of #Lee #Foss’ Cold As Ice stood in #1 for almost 4 weeks on #Beatport), and now that his album will be released later this year he claims he is “not nervous at all, just very excited” about it.
But the expectations are high.. His first EP received many amazing reviews and accolades such as Ibiza Voice’s 7.5, and #MixMag’s “Tune Of The Month” and the amazing #5 #out #of #5 stars.
In 2013 Louie released his second EP on No.19 by the name of #Autophobia, featuring the stunning vocals of #LUNA, which got the remix treatment by none other than his label mates #Art #Department. In the same month Autophobia was released Louie also had 2 magnificent releases which made a big splash in the scene. The first one was a release on Shir Khan’s imprint #Exploited of a collaboration with #Betoko and #Fritz #Helder from #Azari #& #III which got to the top 10 Deep House charts on #Beatport, while his first EP on his own #MEXA Records called #New #Hateration got to the #1 spot again on the Nu Disco charts with the remix done by none other than house legend #MK.

Shok is a producer, musician, multi-instrumentalist. His use of bass guitar, guitar and even live drums (including live tambourine) and his own voice as backing vocals, set his sound apart from the usual fully electronic remix.

Notable remixes include Fischerspooner, The BellRays (Lisa K of The Basement Jaxx), Nick Cave and Warren Ellis's Grinderman, Mirah, KMFDM, Combichrist, Fun Lovin Criminals, Isaac Hayes & Burt Bacharach, Godhead, autoKratz, featuring bassist, Peter Hook (Joy Division / New Order), Daniel Myer's Architect and Haujobb.

Recently having wrapped a mix for the new UK sensation, Queen Of Hearts, he is currently remixing Neil Finn (Crowded House, Split Enz) for the Pajama Club album, Max Pashm and Gotye.

Production and collaborative credits include work with Josie Cotton, Lady Gaga, DJ Superstar Keoki, L7's Donita Sparks, Traci Lords, Douglas McCarthy (Nitzer Ebb), Technical Itch and Daniel Ash (Bauhaus / Love And Rockets).

Shok has composed music for Nickelodeon cartoons, A&E’e Biography, Paramount Pictures, Fox, Miramax, M. Night Shyamalon, PS3, Newgrounds and Michael Bay’s Transformers in a musical collaboration with Adam Freeland, Bassbin Twins and Alex Metric.

He has been the drummer of Mount Sims and Thrill Kill Kult, Red Light District (1920s, 30s neo-vaudeville cabaret vs. a time machine), worked with Juno Reactor and is part of Zeitmahl and Tres Vampires, a project with Johnette Napolitano of Concrete Blonde and David J. of Bauhaus / Love And Rockets set for release 2012.

Metroboy aka Ben Ervine is a producer/DJ from the southwest of England, and forms one half of award-winning breakbeat duo Ben and Lex. Metroboy's music is a crunchy, hard-bleep style of minimal and tech house, with unflinching grooves and uplifting tones sure to lock in any dancefloor. His remix of Benjamin Vial's "The Bass and the Monkey" was released on Plasma.Digital in Feb 2009. Further remixes for Ape and VIM records are in the pipeline.

Since Sept 2007 MetroBoy has hosted a bi-monthly tech house, minimal and techno show on Brap.FM featuring the latest sounds from Minus, Get Physical and Berlin as well as many other quality modern tech producers. A full archive of the show in podcast format is available on the MetroBoy blog - Well worth exploring for some awesome mixage from tech jazz and deep house to crunchy techno.

Long time Watergate resident Matthias Meyer embarks on a momentous summer schedule this year propelled by some career defining moments of late. On the music front, he has continued his quality approach with a small number of high impact releases in recent times including the Beatport Deep House number 1 ‘Hope’ alongside Ryan Davis on his beloved Watergate Records and the Pete Tong endorsed remix of Butch - ‘Shahzrad’ (which made his BBC Radio 1 Tunes of the Year list alongside many established luminaries). These releases join a stellar discography which includes fan favourites such as ‘Reichanbach’, ‘Tout Va Bien’, ‘November Rain’ and of course, ‘Infinity’.

The past few months on the road have also provided some poignant moments for Meyer with visits to the likes of Tobacco Dock, Liverpool’s Circus, Fabrik - Madrid, Rex Paris, Cityfox in New York and of course the renowned Stereo in Montreal. Another of his highlights on the road was a memorable trip to Brazil, playing D-Edge and Warung to universal acclaim. Alongside this the German also found time for a number of pivotal festival appearances (Strawberry Fields in Australia proving to be a particular highlight) and performances at both the Mixmag Lab and Boiler Room, Berlin.

Following on from his well-received residency at Pacha, Ibiza alongside Hot Since 82 last year, Meyer will return to the landmark venue once more this summer as well as venturing further afield to play Ibiza bastions Hï and Heart.

With a style that ranges from uplifting and orchestral to deep tribal grooves, the Berlin based selector will continue to showcase his diverse talents globally throughout the rest of 2018, kicking off the summer with a considerable European tour before his long awaited return to the white isle. Meyer looks set to finish this year just as he started it, with an action packed schedule focused around an expansive US tour.

Biography 
Electronic strolls between the legendary venues of Box and Omen in early 1990s Frankfurt am Main / Germany taught Sebastian Scholz his decidedly house and techno roots.

Roots that, upon his shift in 2000 to Shanghai / China, planted the unexpected beginnings of an electronic musical movement: Sebastian coorganized the first show for Sven Väth in Shanghai and launched Shanghai's premier Electronic Art Platform micro. The platform instigated China's first Ableton Live Music Production Workshop, various Shanghai Jazz Scene collaborations and a thriving number of artistic installations, events and performances. 

Since 2011 Sebastian Scholz is back in Europe and worked in Frankfurt / Germany and around the world for Sven Väths international Cocoon Event Agency. Inbetween he played in clubs like Cocoon / Frankfurt, Batofar / Paris, Club der Visionäre / Berlin and Klunkerkranich / Berlin. 

In summer 2014 Sebastian Scholz finally moved to Berlin, is continously working on his releases and can bee booked worldwide under licence of Pearls Booking Berlin.

Biografie ///

Elektronische Spaziergänge zwischen den legendären Clubs Box und Omen Anfang der 1990er Jahre in Frankfurt am Main legten Sebastian Scholz dezidierte House und Techno Wurzeln.

Wurzeln, die ihn, nach seinem Umzug im Jahr 2000 nach Shanghai, unerwartet zu einem der Pioniere der elektronischen Musik in China werden ließen: Sebastian Scholz organisierte die erste Show für Sven Väth in Shanghai mit und startete Shanghais führende Plattform für elektronische Musik micro. Die Plattform veranstaltete Chinas ersten Ableton Live Music Production Workshop, knüpfte verschiedene Kooperationen mit der berühmten Shanghaier Jazz Szene und veranstaltete eine erfolgreiche Reihe von Events und Kunstinstallationen, Events und Performances.

Seit 2011 ist Sebastian Scholz zurück in Europa und arbeitete in Frankfurt am Main und weltweit für Sven Väths internationale Cocoon Eventagentur. Dazwischen legte er in Clubs wie Cocoon / Frankfurt, Batofar / Paris, Club der Visionäre / Berlin und Klunkerkranich / Berlin auf.

Im Sommer 2014 zog Sebastian Scholz nach Berlin, arbeitet kontinuierlich an seinen Releases und kann weltweit via Pearls Booking Berlin gebucht werden.
